A. |author-link=Jonathan Silk |date=2003 |title=Dressed for Success: The Monk K\u0101\u015byapa and Strategies of Legitimation in Earlier Mah\u0101y\u0101na Buddhist Scriptures |journal=[[Journal asiatique]] |volume=291 |issue=1\u20132 |pages=173\u2013219 |url=https://openaccess.leidenuniv.nl/bitstream/handle/1887/17730/Silk_Dressed%20For%20Success.pdf?sequence=1 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217191410/https://openaccess.leidenuniv.nl/bitstream/handle/1887/17730/Silk_Dressed%2520For%2520Success.pdf?sequence=1 |archive-date=17 February 2020 |url-status=live}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Strong |first1=J.S. |author-link=John S. Strong |title=The Legend and Cult of Upagupta: Sanskrit Buddhism in North India and Southeast Asia |date=1994 |publisher=[[Motilal Banarsidass Publishers]] |isbn=9788120811546 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=bKq7k2DegjcC}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Strong |first1=J.S. |authorlink1=John S. Strong |title=The Buddha: A Beginner's Guide |date=2001 |publisher=[[Oneworld Publications]] |isbn=978-1-78074-054-6}}\n* {{Citation |title=Relics of the Buddha|first=J.S. |last=Strong|author-link=John S. Strong |year=2007 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=_KLAxmR8PZAC |publisher=[[Princeton University Press]]|isbn=978-0-691-11764-5 }}\n* {{Citation |last1=Swearer|first1=D.K.|title=The Buddhist World of Southeast Asia|date=2010|publisher=[[State University of New York Press]]|isbn=978-1-4384-3251-9|edition=2nd}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Sujato |first1=Bhikkhu |last2=Brahmali |first2=Bhikkhu |title=Authenticity of the Early Buddhist Texts |date=2015 |journal= Journal of the Oxford Centre for Buddhist Studies |volume=5 |url=https://ocbs.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/authenticity.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224032237/http://ocbs.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/authenticity.pdf |archive-date=24 December 2015 |url-status=live}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Tambiah |first1=S.J. |authorlink1=Stanley Jeyaraja Tambiah |title=The Buddhist Saints of the Forest and the Cult of Amulets: A Study in Charisma, Hagiography, Sectarianism, and Millennial Buddhism |date=1984 |publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]] |isbn=978-0-521-27787-7}}\n* {{Citation |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20070614122021/http://dl-gamma.tccd.edu/academic/booklets/sp07/PHIL_1304.pdf |url=http://dl-gamma.tccd.edu/academic/booklets/sp07/PHIL_1304.pdf |archive-date=14 June 2007 |url-status=dead |title=Great Religions of the World |author=[[Tarrant County College]], Center for Distance Learning |ref={{harvid|Tarrant County College, 2007}} |access-date=11 April 2007 }}\n* {{Citation |last=Tilakaratne |first=A. |year=2003 |title=The Role of the Sangha in the Conflict in Sri Lanka |journal=Journal of Buddhist Ethics |volume=10 |url=http://blogs.dickinson.edu/buddhistethics/files/2010/12/Tilakaratne.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190805023557/http://blogs.dickinson.edu/buddhistethics/files/2010/12/Tilakaratne.pdf |archive-date=5 August 2019 |url-status=live |pages=167\u2013191}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Tournier |first1=V. |year=2013 |title=Autour de B\u0101miy\u0101n. De la Bactriane hell\u00e9nis\u00e9e \u00e0 l'Inde bouddhique |language=fr |trans-title=Around B\u0101miy\u0101n: From Hellenized Bactria to Buddhist India |publisher=De Boccard |editor-first=G. |editor-last=Duc\u0153ur |chapter=Mat\u00e9riaux pour une histoire de la l\u00e9gende et du culte de Mah\u0101k\u0101\u015byapa: une relecture d\u2019un fragment inscrit retrouv\u00e9 \u00e0 Silao (Bih\u0101r) |trans-chapter=Materials for a History of the Legend and Cult of Mah\u0101k\u0101\u015byapa: A Rereading of an Inscribed Fragment Found at Silao (Bih\u0101r) |url=https://eprints.soas.ac.uk/17114/1/Tournier%20Kasyapa%20Silao%202012.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190619171841/https://eprints.soas.ac.uk/17114/1/Tournier%20Kasyapa%20Silao%202012.pdf |archive-date=19 June 2019 |url-status=live |oclc=823280495}}\n* {{Citation |last1=Tournier |first1=V. 